<!-- Funding -->
<div id="funding-help" class="help-text">
	<h4>Funding</h4>
	<p>On this screen you can select the funding stream(s) that will likely fund the theme (target market, core services, infrastructure support), and enter how this stream could address the theme.</p>
	<p>E.g Target Market Theme, Trusts and Foundations selected: "Funding is available from the Children's Foundation which seek to promote aspirations of ethnic groups."</p>
	<p>Core Services Theme, Public Grants selected: "Arts Council fund learning initiatives for schools."</p>
	<p>Infrastructure Support Theme, Major Donor selected: "Doners recently expressed an interest in improving heritage materials."</p>
</div>

<!-- Constraints -->
<div id="constraints-help" class="help-text">
	<h4>Constraints</h4>
	<p>On this screen you can add whatever constraints might be relevant to each of the themes you selected on the Theme Screen. Each theme will likely have one or more constraints that you can describe in the text boxes. E.g.:</p>
	<p>Target Market:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Operational Constraint, 'Yes' selected "Lack of staff resources."</li>
		<li>Financial Constraint 'No' selected "Funding likely to be secured."</li>
		<li>Political Constraint 'Yes' selected "Target group is not current council priority."</li>
	</ul>
	<p>Core Services:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Operational Constraint, 'Yes' selected "Lack of staff resources."</li>
		<li>Financial Constraint 'No' selected "Funding likely to be secured."</li>
		<li>Political Constraint 'No' selected "Counsellors want more heritage in schools."</li>
	</ul>
	<p>Infrastructure Support:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Operational Constraint, 'Yes' selected "Lack of staff resources."</li>
		<li>Financial Constraint 'Yes' selected "materials development expensive."</li>
		<li>Political Constraint 'Yes' selected "Counsellors prefer to support more high profile projects."</li>
	</ul>
</div>

<!-- Action -->
<div id="action-help" class="help-text">
	<h4>Action</h4>
	<p>On this screen you can begin to pull the project together and set out a pathway to get started. I.e.:</p> 
	<p><strong>Vision:</strong> what is the key sales line to make people enthused with doing this?</p> 
	<p><strong>1st Steps:</strong> what tasks will you do first to start it off?</p> 
	<p><strong>Discomfort:</strong> how do you make whoever is comfortable with not doing it uncomfortable with the status quo?</p> 
</div>
